# Retail Demand Forecasting System

An intelligent system for automating retail replenishment decisions with machine learning, interactive analytics, and an AI copilot for forecast-based decision support.

## Overview

This project combines classical demand forecasting workflows with an application layer that makes results usable for business users. The system is designed to help procurement teams, supply planners, and operations managers:

- forecast item-level demand
- compare trained forecasting models
- review quality metrics in a compact dashboard
- ask natural-language questions about forecasts
- estimate replenishment quantities using current stock, safety stock, and lead time

The application includes:

- a **FastAPI backend** for model access and business logic
- a **static frontend UI** served by the backend
- an **LLM-based retail copilot** with tool-calling for forecast, explanation, and order recommendations
- a **notebook-driven experimentation layer** for training and artifact preparation

---

## Key Features

### 1. Forecasting API
Query demand forecasts for a specific store, item, and date or date range.

### 2. Model Comparison and Metrics
Inspect global metrics such as RMSE, R², WAPE, and MAE, and compare available trained models.

### 3. Business-Friendly UI
The frontend provides several pages for demonstration and documentation:

- **Home** – project summary, available models, global metrics
- **Predict** – select store, item, date, and model for forecast lookup
- **Analytics** – compact view of model quality metrics
- **Agent** – chat-based forecasting and replenishment assistant
- **About** – project purpose and workflow overview

### 4. AI Procurement Copilot
The agent can:

- return factual forecasts
- explain predictions using model feature importance
- recommend order quantities
- turn technical outputs into business language

---

## System Architecture

```text
User / Browser
      |
      v
Frontend UI (static HTML/CSS/JS)
      |
      v
FastAPI Backend
  |       |         |
  |       |         +--> Agent service (LLM + tool calling)
  |       +------------> Metrics service
  +--------------------> Predictor service
                          |
                          v
                 Artifact loader / trained model outputs
```

### Backend responsibilities

- serve API endpoints
- load trained artifacts and metadata
- return forecasts and metrics
- expose an agent endpoint for natural-language interaction
- serve the frontend pages and static assets

### Frontend responsibilities

- show project overview
- collect prediction inputs
- display model metrics
- provide a chat interface for the assistant

---

## Project Structure

```text
retail-demand-forecasting-system/
└── app/
    ├── backend/
    │   ├── api/              # FastAPI routes
    │   ├── models/           # Pydantic schemas
    │   ├── prompts/          # Agent prompt templates
    │   ├── services/         # Prediction, metrics, loader, LLM, agent logic
    │   ├── utils/            # Logging and helper utilities
    │   ├── main.py           # FastAPI app entry point
    │   ├── requirements.txt  # Backend dependencies
    │   └── settings.py       # Environment-driven configuration
    ├── frontend/             # Static UI pages and assets
    └── notebooks/            # Experiments, training, and analysis notebooks
```

