## Tech Stack

### Backend
- FastAPI
- Uvicorn
- Pydantic / pydantic-settings
- Pandas
- NumPy
- scikit-learn
- XGBoost
- LightGBM
- Jinja2
- httpx

### Frontend
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript

### ML / Forecasting
- trained forecasting artifacts loaded from the artifact directory
- baseline and tree-based models
- model quality evaluation through regression metrics

### LLM Integration
- OpenRouter-compatible chat completion endpoint
- tool-calling agent flow for structured forecast operations

---

## Available API Endpoints

### Health
- `GET /health` – service health check
- `GET /agent/health` – agent health check

### Data helpers
- `GET /data/families`
- `GET /data/stores`
- `GET /data/items`
- `GET /data/items-labeled`
- `GET /data/models`

### Metrics
- `GET /metrics/global`
- `GET /metrics/model_info`

### Forecasting
- `GET /predict/timeseries`

Example:

```bash
curl "http://127.0.0.1:8000/predict/timeseries?store=44&item=5&date_from=2017-07-16"
```

### Agent
- `POST /agent/chat`

Example:

```bash
curl -X POST "http://127.0.0.1:8000/agent/chat" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "message": "What is the forecast for Item 5 in Store 44 on 2017-07-16?",
    "context": {},
    "history": []
  }'
```

